+### M3 — `rotate-telegram-bot.sh:172-189` retry loop fragile to malformed responses
+
+```bash
+response=$(curl -sS "${TELEGRAM_BASE}/bot${OLD_TOKEN}/getMe")
+ok_field=$(echo "$response" | jq -r '.ok')
+```
+
+A transient 5xx with empty body → `curl -sS` exits 0 with empty stdout → `jq -r` errors → under `set -e` the assignment can exit the script mid-retry, defeating the 5×30s buffer. Wrap with `|| echo unknown` and treat `unknown` as "retry" instead of crashing.
